ZCZC GE05
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
SATURDAY TO TUESDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND
COASTGUARD AGENCY AT 102300 UTC
THE WEATHER PATTERN OVER THE UK WILL BE GENERALLY
CYCLONIC THROUGH THE WEEKEND. ONE AREA OF LOW PRESSURE
NEAR THE SCOTTISH WERN ISLES WILL MOV NWARDS TO ICELAND.
ANOTHER LOW CENTRE WILL MOV NEWARDS TO LIE NEAR SERN
IRELAND BY THE END OF SUNDAY WITH TROUGHS OF LOW
PRESSURE EXTENDING TO NEAR HOLLAND. THERE IS MORE
UNCERTAINTY AS WE GO THROUGH MONDAY AND TUESDAY BUT
LIKELY TO REMAIN VERY UNSETTLED WITH CYCLONIC CONDITIONS
OVER THE UK AND ATLANTIC SEA AREAS. THROUGH SATURDAY
EVENING AND SUNDAY WINDS WILL BE BROADLY SE AND STRG AT
TIMES PERHAPS EVEN WITH GALES IN THE N FOR A TIME.
ALTHOUGH THERE IS SOME UNCERTAINTY IN DETAIL LATER IN THE
PERIOD WINDS WILL CONTINUE STRG AT TIMES THROUGH MONDAY
AND TUESDAY WITH THE RISK OF GALES ESPECIALLY IN THE
SERN PART OF THE N SEA AND THAMES DOVER AND WIGHT
NNNN